  "prompt": "At age 25, it is too young for marry to my girlfriend?",
  "response": "Whether 25 is too young to marry depends on various factors, including your relationship, goals, and personal readiness. Here are some things to consider:\n\n1. **Relationship Maturity**: Have you and your girlfriend been together long enough to understand each other deeply? Do you handle conflicts well and share similar values and life goals?\n\n2. **Personal Readiness**: Are you emotionally and financially ready for marriage? Marriage requires commitment, responsibility, and sometimes sacrifices. It\u2019s important to feel secure in your career, finances, and personal growth.\n\n3. **Life Goals**: Do you both align on major life decisions, such as having children, career aspirations, or where you want to live? These factors can impact your long-term compatibility.\n\n4. **Support System**: Do you have a strong support system of family and friends who can guide and support you as you navigate married life?\n\n5. **Cultural and Social Factors**: In some cultures or communities, marrying at 25 is common, while in others, it might be considered young. Consider your own cultural and social context.\n\nUltimately, there\u2019s no \u201cright\u201d age to get married\u2014it\u2019s about being ready and confident in your decision. Take time to reflect on your relationship and discuss your future together openly with your girlfriend. If you\u2019re unsure, there\u2019s no harm in waiting until you feel more prepared.",
